THREE men have admitted being involved in an armed heist at Glasgow's Argyll Arcade.Jason Yendall, Aaron Brannan and Jason Britton raided a jewellery shop at the mall bagging more than &pound;200,000 of high-end watches. They were linked to the crime after two friends - Alistair Oliver and Gordon McLay - were later seen sporting two of the stolen watches at their local bookies.All five were also involved in a bank robbery in Edinburgh in which &pound;20,000 was taken.The gang face lengthy jail terms when they are sentenced next month.